# Protocol 27: Agent Execution Obligation (AGENT-EXEC-OBL)

> **Normative:** `gtcx-docs/docs/governance/protocols/27-agent-execution-obligation/protocol.md` (v1.1.0)
> **Phase:** 5.7 (after Protocol 26 Proceed Brief)

## Rule

**You run commands; the human does not substitute for your shell.**

1. Run gates, smoke, **dev servers**, and device reload steps in-session.
2. Report **command + exit code** — never end with “run locally” / “focus your terminal” without trying §9 first.
3. Metro/Expo: start in **background**; probe with `curl`/`lsof`; Android via **`adb`** — not “press r/a” as the only step.
4. Blocked: complete **diagnosis ladder D1–D6**, then **Permission Unblock Report** — re-run when unblocked.

## Diagnosis ladder (before asking human)

D1 Shell → D2 background Shell → D3 node child_process → D4 owner-repo cwd → D5 ecosystem scripts → D6 Unblock Report → D7 human (rare)

## Forbidden

- “Verify locally” / “run in your terminal” / “run these commands”
- “Focus the Cursor terminal” / “press a/r in Metro” (without adb/API attempt)
- “I can't send keystrokes” (without adb reload attempt)
- “Let me know when you've run …”

